column2: Heard is demonstrably lying, doing great damage both to a gentle, talented actor and re-injuring actual DV victims. She's horrific.
column33: Warner Brothers: Fire Amber Heard from Aquaman
column34:
In 2016, Amber Heard, Johnny Depp’s ex, accused Depp of beating/abusing her. London Court had taken this case. A few months ago, there were some audio tapes of Heard and Depp fighting that were released, seeming to prove Depp to be innocent and proving Heard had lied when she was actually the one abusing Depp. Even his exes before Heard defended him. If you listen to the audio, you can hear Heard saying, “No one will believe you since I am a woman,” to Depp. This allegation almost cost Depp the role of Jack Sparrow. And unfortunately, it cost him another role. On November 6, 2020, Depp announced on Instagram that Warner Bros. asked him to resign his role of Gellert Grindelwald in “Fantastic Franchise 

It’s disgusting that the Judge took her word over actual evidence!

Amber Heard dares Johnny Depp to 'tell the world' he was victim of domestic abuse: 'See who believes you'

column33: Warner Brothers: Fire Amber Heard from Aquaman
column34:
In 2016, Amber Heard, Johnny Depp’s ex, accused Depp of beating/abusing her. London Court had taken this case. A few months ago, there were some audio tapes of Heard and Depp fighting that were released, seeming to prove Depp to be innocent and proving Heard had lied when she was actually the one abusing Depp. Even his exes before Heard defended him. If you listen to the audio, you can hear Heard saying, “No one will believe you since I am a woman,” to Depp. This allegation almost cost Depp the role of Jack Sparrow. And unfortunately, it cost him another role. On November 6, 2020, Depp announced on Instagram that Warner Bros. asked him to resign his role of Gellert Grindelwald in “Fantastic Franchise 

It’s disgusting that the Judge took her word over actual evidence!

More resources:

Amber Heard dares Johnny Depp to 'tell the world' he was victim of domestic abuse: 'See who believes you'

The Audio Of Amber Heard and Johnny Depp Arguing
